post_text:
Welcome to the Union County Government page. We are so glad you are interested in learning more about Union County, Georgia. Whether you are looking for adventure or solitude, Union County has it all.

Venture out and explore the expansive natural beauty of our area, complete with majestic waterfalls, invigorating hiking trails and crystal clear lakes, or gather with friends and family at one of our state-of-the-art facilities, including our Horse Arena, Farmers Market or Union County Community Center. Union County has it all and we welcome you to our community.

Suches is an unincorporated area in Union County in the Georgia mountains, about 2 hours north of Atlanta. With an altitude of around 3,000 ft. Suches is blessed with clean mountain air and cool temperatures.

We ask that you make positive and/or respectful post contributions to the Union County Facebook page without hate speech, bullying, promotions, or spam. We also ask that you respect personal privacy. Thank you.

ARE YOU REPRESENTED?

Just as the U.S. House of Representatives is reapportioned, or rearranged, after each census, the Georgia General Assembly arranges the districts within the Georgia House of Representatives and the Georgia Senate to ensure that each district is represented according to constituent population. Represent by visiting https://2020census.gov/ Thanks in advance. #EveryOneCounts

Al Garnto is feeling blessed with Beverly Zoe Bradley.
July 27 at 9:27 PM ¬∑

I am always honored for the opportunity to make new sculptures for my home-town of Blairsville, Georgia! Here are three new sculptures in my Appalachian Sculpture Project for Meeks Park. These metal folk art floral sculptures have been gaining a lot of momentum the last couple of years, I am very excited to have some of these here now in my home-town.
With such a beautifully designed building that Garland Reynolds Jr. has done here, along with this gorgeous landscape designed by, Beverly Zoe Bradley, it really makes an old country boy‚Äôs work like myself look pretty good. Thank you, Garland and Beverly!
Meeks Park has been a huge blessing not only to my life, but to the life of this community! How fortunate we are to have such and outstanding park as this to call our own. So in closing, I just want to say Thank You, Meeks Park, for all you have done in the advancement of this home-town boy‚Äôs art career over the years. I am so grateful for all the exposure you have afforded me. I appreciate you all!
God Is Good

Physicians, physician assistants, nurse practitioners and other medical staff gathered in the Union County High School gym during the week of July 13-17, to conduct the required annual physical exams for students in the schools‚Äô athletic programs. These physicals were conducted with COVID-19 precautions in place.

Medical staff from Union General Hospital have been providing this service to the community for over 20 years. They take time from their busy practices to help ensure local students are able to participate in sports. The physical exams are free to the students and there were almost 300 students seen this year.

A special thank you to all of the participating health care professionals this year ‚Äì as well as the Union County High School for hosting this annual event.

post_text: Did you know that the information received from US Census Surveys impacts the amount of federal funding we receive in Georgia? More money goes to places where more people live. Did you know that it impacts how/when GA roads are improved? Did you know that the number of seats GA has in congress depends upon the population count?...and the Census is one of the tools used to determine that number. Political districts at the federal, state, and local levels are drawn based on population data. So without an accurate count, it is impossible to ensure that people‚Äôs votes will have the same weight. Knowing who lives where and knowing how the population is changing is also critical for long-term planning, as cities and communities try to make informed decisions about where to invest in services like new transportation modes or more schools. Please complete and return your Census survey. Union County needs each resident to be counted. Thank you!

Union County Schools, along with Union General Hospital, will be offering free physicals to all UCS athletes trying-out and participating in a sport for the 2020-2021 school year.

Physicals will be held in the UCHS gym, and all athletes must enter through the back doors by the weight room. All athletes need to bring the completed forms prior to their physical.

Forms can be downloaded at: (Scroll down a little)

https://sites.google.com/ucschools.org/ucsathletics/uchs

Please have your athletes report at the following dates and times:

Monday July 13th: Middle School Football, Softball, Volleyball, Woody Gap,Girls Basketball
Wednesday July 15th: Cross Country/Track, Golf, Cheer,
Thursday July 16th: Baseball, Band,Wrestling, Woody Gap, Girls Soccer
Friday July 17th: High School Football, Swim,Woody Gap, Boys Basketball, Boys Soccer

post_text: Suches, Georgia: The Run Above the Clouds race is the kickoff event for the Indian Summer Festival, which is held on the first full weekend in October. The Run Above the Clouds offers 10K and 5K road races over a beautifully scenic, challenging out-and-back course through the North Georgia mountains. There is also a 1-mile Fun Run & Dog Jog, over a mostly flat course.

post_text:
Suches, Georgia: The Suches Fire Department was organized in 1984 as a part of the new county-wide fire department and was quartered in a single bay building with the voting precinct. We shortly moved across the parking lot to a new, larger building and when it was enlarged still further to provide us a day room and training space, the voting precinct followed us. The original building is now used for other community purposes.

Nearly two dozen men were trained as basic firefighters (a twenty hour course) and the equipment consisted of a Georgia Forestry Commission rural fire defense "fireknocker" (still in service as Tanker 11). Over the years we have increased our level of training and equipment. The two dozen men and women in the department now train to a basic 60 hour course and many are certified as first class firefighters. Many are emergency medical first responders and several are EMTs or Paramedics.

post_text:
The Suches Community Center was one of the first projects to receive funding from the 2008 Special Purpose Local Option Sales Tax.

The Union County School System had recently completed replacement of the old gym at the Woody Gap School and donated the reclaimed elements of the building to the county. This formed the nucleus of the reconstructed gym which is now a part of the community center. Added to the front of this was space for a large kitchen, two meeting rooms, rest rooms and some storage space.

The facility has been furnished with help from the Suches Fire Department, Union County Rec Department, the Union County Library and Zion Baptist Church as well as other agencies and too many Suches residents to mention.

A committee of Suches residents manages the operation of the center under the oversight of the Union County Recreation Department. Policies and fee schedules have been developed to encourage community use at reasonable rates while still being good stewards of county resources.

post_text: The Suches, Georgia feature series: Suches is an unincorporated area in Union County in the Georgia mountains, about 2 hours north of Atlanta. With an altitude of around 3,000 ft. Suches is blessed with clean mountain air and cool temperatures, typically 5 to 8 degrees lower than Atlanta. More info can be found at: http://www.suches.com
